threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Renesas SH, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is an IoT malware downloader targeting the RISC-V (rv32gc) architecture. The binary exhibits multiple malicious behaviors including attempting to download and execute secondary payloads using a variety of methods (wget, tftp, curl, ftpget, and raw HTTP GET requests). It also contains logic to kill competing processes by iterating through `/proc` and terminating executables that are deleted or running from hidden paths. Additionally, it attempts to prevent termination by the OOM killer by modifying `/proc/self/oom_score_adj`. The presence of a Telegram URL (`t.me/disconnect`) and command strings for downloading and executing scripts (`/wget.sh`, `chmod 777 ...; ./...`) are strong indicators of its malicious intent, characteristic of a botnet agent.
